# Noetfield — ASK POLICY (superseded → CPL v1.1)

**Binding law:** [000-noetfield-universal-change-preservation-law-v1.1.mdc](000-noetfield-universal-change-preservation-law-v1.1.mdc) — **NOETFIELD AUTONOMOUS CHANGE-PRESERVATION LAW v1.1**

This file no longer requires founder permission before routine scoped work. The old ask-before-every-edit posture is retired.

## Core

Execute autonomously. Preserve unrelated work.

The user’s task instruction is authority for ordinary scoped work. Infer the smallest reasonable scope and proceed.

## Do not ask for routine permission

Do not ask before: inspect; fetch; isolated branch/worktree; scoped edits; shell; declared deps; build/test/lint/verify; retry reversible failures; commit; open/update PR; receipts; in-scope repair.

Perform preflight automatically. Do not stop merely to report it. Put results in the final receipt.

## Ask founder only when

1. Action would destroy or overwrite unrelated work
2. Material contradiction cannot be safely resolved
3. Destructive migration, deletion, force-push, history rewrite, credential/authority change, money movement, contract/legal action, or irreversible external send is required
4. Merge or production deploy is required but not authorized by the current instruction or standing authority
5. Exact production baseline cannot be established and continuing could downgrade

## Default flow

```
Task → infer scope → isolated lane → execute → verify preservation → receipt + verdict
```

